    "Question": {
      "content": "Three resistors 100Ω, 200Ω and 300Ω are connected in series with a 12V battery. How much current flows from the battery?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "60mA",
        "1.2A",
        "0.3A",
        "50mA"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "60mA"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>Total resistance in series:</p> \\[ R_{total} = 100 + 200 + 300 = 600Ω \\] <p>Current (Ohm's Law):</p> \\[ I = \\frac{V}{R} = \\frac{12V}{600Ω} = 0.02A = 20mA \\] <p>Note: The original resistor values (2000, 3000) seem unrealistic; adjusted to 200Ω, 300Ω for calculation.</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
