    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 42 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A battery of emf 12V and internal resistance 2Ω is connected to a resistor of 16Ω. Which is the potential difference of the battery?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "21.2V",
        "10.66V",
        "0.75V",
        "24V"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "10.66V"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>Terminal voltage calculation: \\[ I = \\frac{ε}{R + r} = \\frac{12}{16 + 2} = 0.666A \\] \\[ V = ε - Ir = 12 - (0.666×2) ≈ 10.66V \\]</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
